     1‚Üí# Changelog
     2‚Üí
     3‚Üí## 2.4.0
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí- Added
     6‚Üí  - TOML v1.1.0 compatibility
     7‚Üí  - Binary wheels for Windows arm64
     9‚Üí## 2.3.0
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí- Added
    12‚Üí  - Binary wheels for Python 3.14 (also free-threaded)
    13‚Üí- Performance
    14‚Üí  - Reduced import time
    16‚Üí## 2.2.1
    17‚Üí
    18‚Üí- Fixed
    19‚Üí  - Don't attempt to compile binary wheels for Python 3.8, 3.9 and 3.10 where cibuildwheel depends on a conflicting Tomli version
    21‚Üí## 2.2.0
    22‚Üí
    23‚Üí- Added
    24‚Üí  - mypyc generated binary wheels for common platforms
    26‚Üí## 2.1.0
    27‚Üí
    28‚Üí- Deprecated
    29‚Üí  - Instantiating `TOMLDecodeError` with free-form arguments.
    30‚Üí    `msg`, `doc` and `pos` arguments should be given.
    31‚Üí- Added
    32‚Üí  - `msg`, `doc`, `pos`, `lineno` and `colno` attributes to `TOMLDecodeError`
    34‚Üí## 2.0.2
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí- Removed
    37‚Üí  - Python 3.7 support
    38‚Üí- Improved
    39‚Üí  - Make `loads` raise `TypeError` not `AttributeError` on bad input types that do not have the `replace` attribute.
    40‚Üí    Improve error message when `bytes` is received.
    41‚Üí- Type annotations
    42‚Üí  - Type annotate `load` input as `typing.IO[bytes]` (previously `typing.BinaryIO`).
    44‚Üí## 2.0.1
    45‚Üí
    46‚Üí- Improved
    47‚Üí  - Make bundling easier by using relative imports internally and adding license and copyright notice to source files.
    48‚Üí  - Make error messages more uniform
    49‚Üí  - Raise a friendly `TypeError` for wrong file mode
    50‚Üí  - Allow `parse_float` to return objects having the `append` attr
    51‚Üí  - Eagerly raise an error if `parse_float` returns an illegal type
    52‚Üí- Packaging
    53‚Üí  - Move from `pytest` testing framework to `unittest` and remove `python-dateutil` test dependency.
    54‚Üí    Tests now only require Python interpreter.
    56‚Üí## 1.2.3
    57‚Üí
    58‚Üí- Fixed
    59‚Üí  - Backport: Allow lower case "t" and "z" in datetimes
    61‚Üí## 2.0.0
    62‚Üí
    63‚Üí- Removed
    64‚Üí  - Python 3.6 support
    65‚Üí  - Support for text file objects as `load` input. Use binary file objects instead.
    66‚Üí  - First argument of `load` and `loads` can no longer be passed by keyword.
    67‚Üí- Fixed
    68‚Üí  - Allow lower case "t" and "z" in datetimes
    69‚Üí- Improved
    70‚Üí  - Raise an error when dotted keys define values outside the "current table".
    71‚Üí    Technically speaking TOML v1.0.0 does allow such assignments
    72‚Üí    but that isn't intended by specification writers,
    73‚Üí    and will change in a future specification version (see the [pull request](https://github.com/toml-lang/toml/pull/848)).
    75‚Üí## 1.2.2
    76‚Üí
    77‚Üí- Fixed
    78‚Üí  - Illegal characters in error messages were surrounded by two pairs of quotation marks
    79‚Üí- Improved
    80‚Üí  - `TOMLDecodeError.__module__` is now the public import path (`tomli`) instead of private import path (`tomli._parser`)
    81‚Üí  - Eliminated an import cycle when `typing.TYPE_CHECKING` is `True`.
    82‚Üí    This allows `sphinx-autodoc-typehints` to resolve type annotations.
    84‚Üí## 1.2.1
    85‚Üí
    86‚Üí- Fixed
    87‚Üí  - Raise an error if a carriage return (without a following line feed) is found in a multi-line basic string
    88‚Üí- Type annotations
    89‚Üí  - Type annotate `load` input as `typing.BinaryIO` only to discourage use of deprecated text file objects.
    90‚Üí- Packaging
    91‚Üí  - Remove legacy `setup.py` from PyPI source distribution.
    92‚Üí    If you're a packager and absolutely need this file, please create an issue.
    94‚Üí## 1.2.0
    95‚Üí
    96‚Üí- Deprecated
    97‚Üí  - Text file objects as input to `load`.
    98‚Üí    Binary file objects should be used instead to avoid opening a TOML file with universal newlines or with an encoding other than UTF-8.
   100‚Üí## 1.1.0
   101‚Üí
   102‚Üí- Added
   103‚Üí  - `load` can now take a binary file object
   105‚Üí## 1.0.4
   106‚Üí
   107‚Üí- Performance
