   140‚Üí## 0.2.9
   141‚Üí
   142‚Üí- Fixed
   143‚Üí  - `TOMLDecodeError` now raised when opening a table implicitly created by a key/value pair
   144‚Üí  - Don't error when two array-of-tables items open a subtable with the same name
   145‚Üí  - Don't error when opening parent table of an already defined array-of-tables item
   147‚Üí## 0.2.8
   148‚Üí
   149‚Üí- Performance
   150‚Üí  - Significant boost to comment parsing speed
   152‚Üí## 0.2.7
   153‚Üí
   154‚Üí- Added
   155‚Üí  - Improved `TOMLDecodeError` error messages.
   156‚Üí    Line and column are included when applicable.
   158‚Üí## 0.2.6
   159‚Üí
   160‚Üí- Performance
   161‚Üí  - Over 5% boost
   163‚Üí## 0.2.5
   164‚Üí
   165‚Üí- Fixed
   166‚Üí  - Made exception type `TOMLDecodeError` when overwriting a value with a deeply nested table
   168‚Üí## 0.2.4
   169‚Üí
   170‚Üí- Fixed
   171‚Üí  - `TOMLDecodeError` is now raised when attempting to overwrite a value in an inline table's or array's namespace with a table definition
   173‚Üí## 0.2.3
   174‚Üí
   175‚Üí- Fixed
   176‚Üí  - Error type was not TOMLDecodeError in some obscure cases
   178‚Üí## 0.2.2
   179‚Üí
   180‚Üí- Added
   181‚Üí  - `tomli.load` for parsing IO streams returned by `open()`
   182‚Üí  - `parse_float` keyword argument to `tomli.loads`.
   183‚Üí    Allows parsing TOML floats to a non-float type in Python.
   185‚Üí## 0.2.1
   186‚Üí
   187‚Üí- Fixed
   188‚Üí  - `TOMLDecodeError` is now raised for duplicate keys in inline tables,
